Files in this project derived from secure-the-mint (renamed; puzzle LOGIC
unchanged from upstream — Apache-2.0 §4(b) "stating that You changed the files"):

  puzzles/lazy_mint_pre_launcher.clsp      <- secure_the_mint_launcher.clsp
  puzzles/lazy_mint_direct_delegate.clsp   <- secure_the_mint_direct_delegate.clsp
  puzzles/lazy_mint_offer_delegate.clsp    <- secure_the_mint_offer_delegate.clsp
  puzzles/lazy_mint_pre_launcher.clsp.hex      (compiled output of the above)
  puzzles/lazy_mint_direct_delegate.clsp.hex   (compiled output of the above)
  puzzles/lazy_mint_offer_delegate.clsp.hex    (compiled output of the above)

The Rust builders in `core/src/lazy_mint.rs` reproduce the secure-the-mint coin
layout (the "secure the bag" tree of fixed coin-spends + the pre-launcher
announcement-securing trick) and cite the source in-file.

The vendored ChiaLisp include `include/curry-and-treehash.clib` is from the
chia-blockchain project (Apache-2.0), used by the ported puzzles.
